===Etymology===
For the noun: Old English ''[[acount]]'', ''account'', ''[[accompt]]'', Old French ''[[acont]]'', from ''[[aconter]]''. Also for the verb: Old English ''[[acounten]]'', ''[[accompten]]'', Old French ''[[aconter]], ''[[à]]'' (Latin ''[[ad]]'') + ''[[conter]]'' to count. French ''conter'' to tell, ''[[compter]]'' to count, Latin ''[[computare]]''. See [[count]].
